      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Josiah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Josiah" href="/user/show/1548582-josiah">Josiah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1548582-josiah?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer208187561" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16674435423451780775">While an interesting story I feel it bares mentioning, although listed as a &quot;Christian&quot; fantasy on Amazon.com, it is not of the Evangelical Christian Faith in nature. While biblical names are used and its ideals and beliefs bare resemblance to Christianity they are not Christian in origin, rather LDS (Mormon) in nature. Still an enjoyable read. Yet I would caution any Evangelical Christian to be aware of its LDS doctrine and principles.<br/>As far as writing goes, the author&apos;s characters were a bit f</span>
  <span id="freeText16674435423451780775" style="display:none">While an interesting story I feel it bares mentioning, although listed as a "Christian" fantasy on Amazon.com, it is not of the Evangelical Christian Faith in nature. While biblical names are used and its ideals and beliefs bare resemblance to Christianity they are not Christian in origin, rather LDS (Mormon) in nature. Still an enjoyable read. Yet I would caution any Evangelical Christian to be aware of its LDS doctrine and principles.<br />As far as writing goes, the author's characters were a bit flimsy, his building good but conclusions too swift and weak, and the setting, names and general structure of society too familiar with our own. So while an interesting read not one I would recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16674435423451780775" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


