        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer93327514" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14435625683272492773">The Thorn is a beautiful fantasy story of hope, faith, and miracles set in an earth-like world with two suns and three moons, and an ancient messianic prophesy. The characters drew me in and I wanted to know more. There were a few times when I wished the story to move along, but I appreciated Fraley&apos;s world-building and practiced my patience. These are characters and a land worth cheering for.</span>
  <span id="freeText14435625683272492773" style="display:none">The Thorn is a beautiful fantasy story of hope, faith, and miracles set in an earth-like world with two suns and three moons, and an ancient messianic prophesy. The characters drew me in and I wanted to know more. There were a few times when I wished the story to move along, but I appreciated Fraley's world-building and practiced my patience. These are characters and a land worth cheering for.</span>
